<p><b>Join as:</b></p>
<br>
<b><h1>Volunteer</h1></b>
<h2>Do you have the passion to contribute towards the country’s progress? Join us! You could volunteer with us for a minimum of two hours every week or on and off for events and one-off volunteering opportunities.Register with us and we will get in touch with you soon (please allow us two weeks) through Email and SMS regarding the next orientation programme. At the orientation you will get more information about all of our projects, the causes you can choose and the locations where you can volunteer.</h2>
<a class="btn btn-primary btn-large" href="/vol"><b>Join Now</b></a><br><br>
<b><h1>Donator</h1></b>
<h2>We are one of the India’s independent volunteer organisations enabling many children in orphanages, slums and government schools across India dream of a better future. SVG can sustain its work only if people like you can support us regularly.</h2>
<a class="btn btn-primary btn-large" href="/don"><b>Join Now</b></a><br><br>
<b><h1>Partner</h1></b>
<h2>SVG  NGO has actively partnered with some of the best known companies in India to develop and execute employee engagement programs. The key has been to understand the unique requirement of each company and develop sustainable volunteering models that work across geographies and internal structures.Some of our Colloborations are Aditya Birla Group,Godrej,IBM,ICIC Bank and ICIC Prudential.</h2>
<a class="btn btn-primary btn-large" href="/col"><b>Join Now</b></a><br><br>
<b><h1>Employee</h1></b>
<h2>Careers at SVG are suitable for dynamic people looking to grow as leaders. Remuneration is on par with the best in the sector. Prior volunteering experience with Bhumi preferred, but careers are open to all.</h2>
<a class="btn btn-primary btn-large" href="/emp"><b>Join Now</b></a><br><br>
